commit.message: Bump version to 0.7.1 for request context fix

Revert "Let Flask manage its own request contexts (#108)"

This reverts commit 624c6473788a02b5ea75944ab49335bf1869f5ea.
Update changelog and bump version

Let Flask manage its own request contexts (#108)

* Let Flask manage its own request contexts

* Fix tests for python 3
Use RTD link in readme
Overwrite debug function to do pre_setup and post_teardown (#94)
Fix docs formatting
Prepare 0.6.2 for release
Changed assertRedirects accept all valid redirect status codes (#102)

Add support for Flask choosing the port in LiveServerTestCase (#98)

Following this change, if the `LIVESERVER_PORT` is set to zero, then the port will be chosen by the operating system and the LiveServerTestCase will adapt accordingly. This requires a bit of a hack (unfortunately), but makes testing large amounts of concurrent LiveServerTestCases much safer.
Use a more descriptive error when signals is not supported (#100)
Change docs URL in README (#97)
Use urljoin to assert redirect location instead of string concat

Fix assertMessageFlashed if no messages were flashed. (#96)

Ensure assertMessageFlashed raises error if no messages flashed. Fixes #95
Hotfix for #91: bump version and update changelog

Nest message flashing support under signals checks

Fixes #91
Bump version to 0.6.0 and update changelog
Use python 3 compatible urlparse library
Remove no longer valid pip install option

Make assertRedirects more flexible

Allow for redirects based on relative paths to
SERVER_NAME and absolute URLS (for checking external
redirect URLs)
Add version 0.11.1 of Flask to the test matrix
Use secret key for testing to make newer versions of Flask happy

Avoid sleeping for 1 second between liveserver test cases

Instead, continually ping the expected server
address via the sockets API which greatly speeds
up the time in between test cases.
Introduces LIVESERVER_TIMEOUT as a config option.
Grammatical fixes
Add assert assertMessageFlashed
Add scripts to automate release process
Bump version to 0.5.0 and update changelog
